title: For Sale:  Mini Uzi Repair Section 9mm, 45acp, .22, .41AE
postcontent: You are buying one repair section only. This is the only Mini Uzi Repair Section that is made specifically for the Mini Uzi. This section has the correct single rib on the left rear. Build a dummy gun, a legal semi-auto, or if you have an 07/SOT you can build a legal post sample. No machining required, just grind and fit your front and rear section smooth and weld together(or cut repair section to proper length to fit your front and rear section). If you have an IMI Mini Uzi kit this section will match up perfectly. Or, you can use a full size kit and this repair section to build a Mini. If you have a full auto Mini SMG kit you will need to weld up the cutouts for the bolt feet under the trunnion before welding the sections together. Some full auto features on your parts kit (bolt,lower,sear,etc) will need to be converted to semi auto configuration to be legal. This is not a receiver until front and rear sections are welded and no FFL is required. Please study all BATF and NFA rules before purchasing. By bidding on this auction you certify that you are of legal age and have researched local, state, and federal laws and that it is legal for you to purchase this item. These are in the white and may show some oxidation. I do not ship outside the USA. Please do not bid unless you have a USA mailing/shipping address. Item will be held until checks clear. title: For Sale:  2004 Bushmaster M4A3  AR 15
postcontent:
This is a 2004 Bushmaster M4A3 model AR-15.  For those of you who have been shooting AR's for a while, you know what that means as far as quality.  For those newer to the game, 2004 is before Bushmaster was bought out, retooled, and restaffed resulting in inferior quality rifles.  This era of Bushmaster is when they were better than about anything out there and still are.  Old timers in my training group have frequently asked to buy this rifle but I don't really like them.

I have shot everything from 40 grain to 77 grain out of this and have never had a misfire or jam on the rifle that wasn't due to bad feed lips or bad primers.  This particular model is a heavy barrel with a 74 style comp on it that makes the recoil almost nothing.  

Because these are older pictures they are inaccurate.  The rifle does come with the factory carry handle and 4x scope.  It does NOT come with the ACOG.  The Magpul grip in front does not come with the gun, it now comes with an upgraded BCM gunfighter grip. 

The only appreciable wear on the gun is around where the buffer tube and upper receiver meet (from a lot of sling mounts banging around).

Remember; this is not a DPMS or value brand AR.  This rifle is a work horse and will last generations.  If you don't believe me, ask a gunsmith who has lots of AR experience and they will confirm how good pre-buyout Bushmasters are.

title: For Sale:  Pump Exposed Hammer 12ga.
postcontent: I have an old Pump 12ga shotgun with exposed hammer, it looks like a trench gun but someone has shortened the barrel down to 18 1/4 " shame ! The Brand is HSB & Co. Mod. Rev-o-NOC  . According to what I could locate on the internet HSB was a large hardware co. located in Chicago, Ill. back in the late 1800s & Early 1900s. If you spell the rev-o-noc backwards it spells Con-O-Ver. These guns were manufactured by Marlin and some by Ithaca. I believe this one to be a Marlin.  I believe it was built in 1906 or 1907. I would consider this gun to be non-firing and unsafe for shooting, due to age and internet also stated Marlin put out a warning that these guns were prone to hang firing and unsafe to shoot. 19" chrome barrell,and chrome reciever plate....this is the most rare model of these weapons...produced in November of 1968.

title: For Sale:  Mauser 1871/84 Rifle, Prussian Military, with extras
location: Lakes Region/Bristol, New Hampshire, United States
postcontent:
Nice complete and shoot able 71/84 Mauser Military rifle with Prussian leather ammo pouch and 47 rounds of 11mm ammo.  Nicely marked collectors item which is also functional and accurate.  Leather military ammo pouch made in 1888 is included, along with 2 full boxes of ammo, and a partial box with 7 rounds and 13 brass. (325 grain lead bullet).  Ammo and pouch alone are worth over $250. This is not one of the rifles recently "made up" by Gibbs Rifle Co. for the movie "The Last Samurai", this is the real deal with an original stock and finish.  The Germans used these in their colonial units in Africa in WWI's East Africa campaign where they ran circles around the British, Belgian and Portuguese forces, and also in WWII when they were pulled out of storage and used by Volksstrum units at the end of the war.  The earlier version is known as the "Howth" rifle in Ireland because of their use in the 1916 Easter uprising.
Bore is shiny with good rifling.  It was last fired about 10 years ago.  I have owned this rifle for 40 years and before that it hung on the wall of a sporting goods store for at least 20 years, so it is an early import (not import marked).  Recent unemployment is causing me to sell my good stuff.
